Description: This is a great sounding and playing guitar built from leftover red cedar from a garage door project. The Cedar is a very light but resonant wood, and the whole guitar weights in at around 6.5 lbs. It has a nitrocellulose lacquer finish, and the guitar has a nice crisp resnonace playing without an amp. I went back and forth on the color but ultimately wanted to see the red cedar on tope with the relic'ed finish around the sides and back. The G&L Asat Tribut neck is, I believe, about 10 years old so it's nice, dry and stable, with jumbo frets. Spertzel Tuners are near new. I also sanded and finished with an amber nitro cellulose lacquer. Right now the back has a nice gloss finish that doesn't feel plastic like a poly finish, but could be lightly sanded for a flat or smoother finish. It's a great playing neck c shape neck that is a bit thicker than a modern C but has the same 9.5 radius. The P90 is from Guitar Madness and measures 8.09k. The Fender Bridge pickup, I believe, came from a Japanese fender and measures 7.93k. They sound great together. Hear a demo of the pickups clean and with a Mojomojo overdrive through my vox vt40 amp. here https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=IC41eSXGArc
